at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan was born in 1264, in Brailsford Green, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Henry de Brailsford in 1284, in Brailsford Green, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters."},"et":{"1264–":"1264–Surnud","1259–1304":"1259–1304","1277–1344":"1277–1344","1279–Female":"1279–Surnud","1287–Male":"1287–Surnud","1289–1322":"1289–1322","1264–Female":"1264–Surnud","1304":"1304","1259":"1259","1279":"1279","1322":"1322","1289":"1289","1344":"1344","1277":"1277","1287":"1287","1264":"1264","1284":"1284","about 1289":"umbes 1289","Brailsford Green, Derbyshire, England":"Brailsford Green, Derbyshire, England","Brailsford, Derbyshire, England.":"Brailsford Green, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Brailsford, Derbyshire, England":"Brailsford Green, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1264–":"1264–Kuollut","1259–1304":"1259–1304","1277–1344":"1277–1344","1279–Female":"1279–Kuollut","1287–Male":"1287–Kuollut","1289–1322":"1289–1322","1264–Female":"1264–Kuollut","1304":"1304","1259":"1259","1279":"1279","1322":"1322","1289":"1289","1344":"1344","1277":"1277","1287":"1287","1264":"1264